{
  "_id": "42Gyary7J0onmHML",
  "name": "Ensnaring Strike",
  "type": "spell",
  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><em>Neccessary manual adjustments to the spell:</em></p>\n<ul>\n<li><em>Change Ability Modifier to the one corresponding to your weapon</em></li>\n<li><em>Add an Attack Roll Bonus if your weapon is +1/+2/+3</em></li>\n<li><em>Adjust the second Damage formula with the correct damage die und damage type for your weapon and add a damage bonus if your weapon is +1/+2/+3</em></li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>The spell creates an active effect on the target that does the reoccuring damage. It's save DC is set to 500 in order to prevent the effect from being saved.</em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The next time you hit a creature with a weapon attack before this spell ends, a writhing mass of thorny vines appears at the point of impact, and the target must succeed on a Strength saving throw or be @Compendium[combat-utility-belt.conditionsdnd5e.0mkU8eksNfwd1AZY]{Restrained}&nbsp;by the magical vines until the spell ends. A Large or larger creature has advantage on this saving throw. If the target succeeds on the save, the vines shrivel away.<br /><br />While @Compendium[combat-utility-belt.conditionsdnd5e.0mkU8eksNfwd1AZY]{Restrained} by this spell, the target takes 1d6 piercing damage at the start of each of its turns. A creature @Compendium[combat-utility-belt.conditionsdnd5e.0mkU8eksNfwd1AZY]{Restrained}&nbsp;by the vines or one that can touch the creature can use its action to make a Strength check against your spell save DC. On a success, the target is freed.&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>At Higher Levels.</strong>&nbsp;If you cast this spell using a spell slot of 2nd level or higher, the damage increases by 1d6 for each slot level above 1st.</p>",
